Comments: Two women (one with sash and perfume-vase the other with alabastron: preparation for a visit to the tomb?).
Two women (one with perfume-vase and alabastron the other with a flat basket: preparation for a visit to the tomb). Late.
(Head- except the back- to right and left shoulder with part of the breast of a woman in chiton and himation frontal). From a small vase.
(Feet of a woman standing to left).
Unexplained subjects:on one fragment (Athena Talthybios); on another (Telamon-or Ajax- Aigina); on the two unpublished (pieces of drapery).
Mother seated and maid with baby.
Woman with lyre and woman with sash.

Find Spot: from Hanai Tepe in the Troad
